OL,3,CLong-awaited Hillsborough Law 'will
OL,4,Ccontain a legal duty of candour'
OL,6,FReplying to Mr McDonnell's
OL,7,Fintervention, Mr Byrne agreed.
OL,9,FHe said: "The Prime Minister has the
OL,10,Fball in his court. He has made a
OL,11,Fpersonal commitment to Liverpool, to
OL,12,Fthe Hillsborough families and
OL,13,Fsurvivors of other state-related
OL,14,Fscandals. He is perhaps the most
OL,15,Fqualified Prime Minister in history to
OL,16,Funderstand why this matters.
OL,18,F"But understanding is not enough. We
OL,19,Fneed courage, we need leadership and
OL,20,Fwe need action."
OL,26,@qD@JOUzD@AOU|D@PO]
